name: Maura Healey
tweet: Consumers with concerns about solicitations should contact our Non-Profit Organizations/Public Charities Division at 617-963-2101 or access a complaint form on our website.  For additional tips on donating see our Giving Wisely Advisory.  https://t.co/dHU6mVeC3L

name: Maura Healey
tweet: ✅ Never pay by cash: Pay by check or credit card and make a check out directly to the charity, not the fundraiser or any other individual. Specify, on the check and in writing, whenever possible, the purpose of your donation.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: ✅ Do not give your personal or financial information to anyone soliciting money: Never give out your Social Security number or other personal information. Review the charity’s privacy policy to find out if your information will be shared with outside companies.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: ✅ If you are contacted by a professional fundraiser, ask questions: How much of the money goes to the charity and how much to a professional fundraiser? Is your contribution tax deductible? What does the charity intend to do with any excess contributions that might remain?

name: Maura Healey
tweet: ✅ Check the charity’s website: If you are contributing online, make sure that the website you are visiting belongs to a legitimate and established charity. Be advised that most crowdfunding sites are not charities and many typically take a percentage of your donation as a fee.

name: Maura Healey
tweet: ✅ Give to charities you know and trust: Well-established charities and organizations with support from government agencies can be good places to donate. Our office maintains annual financial reports online. You can also check with the IRS for an organization’s federal Form 990.
